comments.body:
[~xiaochen] Thanks for your review!
{quote}
Any reason to do isEqual here rather than the canonical override equals ?
{quote}
The {{equals}} method in *enum* is final, we can't override it in the sub class such as {{CipherSuite}} and {{CryptoProtocolVersion}}, and the inherited  {{equals}} didn't compare the private variables, so I have to do my own {{isEqual}} in these classes.
 {{EncryptionZoneInt}} could have a override {{equals}}, I'm done with it in the new attached patch.

{quote}
The new readINodeXAttrByPrefixedName method seems unnecessary
{quote}
Agree with that reuse is always better, but the main purpose of the new {{readINodeXAttrByPrefixedName}} is not to get the snapshot ID, it's for the specified {{inode}}. The existing {{readINodeXAttrByPrefixedName}} always use the last inode in {{iip}}, seems not meet requirements in the traversal loop of {{iip}}.

{quote}
getEncryptionZoneForPath: Encryption zones can only be on Dirs, so no point in trying to get an ezi when it's not a dir.
{quote}
done in the new attached patch, thanks for point out this.

{quote}
getEncryptionZoneForPath: I suspect the nullity check is related to some snapshot behavior
{quote}
Did you refer to the {{inode == null}}? It's another expression of the origin {{if(inode != null)}} to make less use of indent since the new added logic have some indents already. I have added some comments for it now, thanks.

Thanks [~xiaochen] for reviewing this again.
{quote}I think we should go with the default Enum#equals comparison
{quote}
Yes, I'm done, use {{EqualsBuilder}} Instead of the new added {{isEqual}} now.
{quote}We can use HashCodeBuilder and EqualsBuilder to implement the EZI equals method.
{quote}
Done in the new attached patch.
{quote}EZI#getEncryptionZoneForPath: can we still use the existing logic to get from encryptionZones?
{quote}
Good idea, done.
{quote}In the new method, parameter name typo 'sanpshotId'.
{quote}
Done, sorry for the typo, and thanks for your carefully review.
